{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866871676,"sessionID":"ses_286162f0cffeY8t2DF73EoXM9P","part":{"id":"prt_d79e9f7f5001yTX8KvR1LPokik","messageID":"msg_d79e9ee2c001cZFjL4Jh6Qg9Uf","sessionID":"ses_286162f0cffeY8t2DF73EoXM9P","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b1670346437546bdb506acb6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This spec covers the K8s/AgentCube Provider functionality in the AgentCube CLI, enabling deployment to either standard Kubernetes (Deployment + Service) or AgentCube's custom AgentRuntime CR.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-026\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Specs**: cli-toolkit/spec.md\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: The AgentCube CLI supports deploying agents to two target providers:\n20: 1. **agentcube**: Uses AgentRuntime CR (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`) for deployment\n21: 2. **k8s**: Uses standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service\n22: \n23: This delta focuses on the provider-specific publish, invoke, and status workflows.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Requirements\n28: \n29: ### Requirement: `publish` command — Provider selection\n30: \n31: The system SHALL support `--provider` option to select deployment target.\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Publish with agentcube provider (default)\n34: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` with `--provider agentcube` (or default)\n35: - **WHEN** metadata contains `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n36: - **THEN** the system SHALL deploy via `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: Publish with k8s provider\n39: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider k8s`\n40: - **WHEN** Kubernetes client initializes successfully\n41: - **THEN** the system SHALL deploy via `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` with NodePort Service\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Publish with k8s provider — NodePort specification\n44: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider k8s --node-port 30080`\n45: - **WHEN** the deployment is created\n46: - **THEN** the Service SHALL use the specified NodePort `30080` (must be 30000-32767)\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Publish with k8s provider — Replicas\n49: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider k8s --replicas 3`\n50: - **WHEN** the deployment is created\n51: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL have `replicas: 3`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Publish with k8s provider — Custom namespace\n54: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider k8s --namespace myns`\n55: - **WHEN** the deployment proceeds\n56: - **THEN** all resources SHALL be created in namespace `myns`\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: `publish` command — AgentCube provider prerequisites\n59: \n60: The system SHALL validate required fields for AgentRuntime CR deployment.\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: Missing router_url\n63: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata lacks `router_url`\n64: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` runs\n65: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring `router_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Missing workload_manager_url\n68: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata lacks `workload_manager_url`\n69: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` runs\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring `workload_manager_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — Standard provider deployment\n73: \n74: The system SHALL create Deployment and NodePort Service for standard K8s provider.\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Deploy agent via KubernetesProvider\n77: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called with valid parameters\n78: - **WHEN** resources are applied to the cluster\n79: - **THEN** the result SHALL include `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Wait for deployment ready\n82: - **GIVEN** a deployment name is provided\n83: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` runs\n84: - **THEN** the system SHALL poll until all replicas are ready or raise `TimeoutError` after 120 seconds\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Delete agent from Kubernetes\n87: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent(agent_name)` is called\n88: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` and ignore 404 errors on individual deletes\n90: \n91: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n92: \n93: The system SHALL create/patch AgentRuntime CR for agentcube provider.\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n96: - **GIVEN** required readiness probe fields exist in metadata\n97: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n98: - **THEN** it SHALL create an AgentRuntime CR with:\n99:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from parameters or environment\n100:   - `sessionTimeout` set to `\"15m\"`\n101:   - `maxSessionDuration` set to `\"8h\"`\n102:   - `imagePullSecrets` as `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR API group and version\n105: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime is created\n106: - **WHEN** the CR is applied to the cluster\n107: - **THEN** it SHALL use `group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, `version: v1alpha1`, `plural: agentruntimes`\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: `invoke` command — Provider routing\n110: \n111: The system SHALL route invocations based on provider.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Invoke via agentcube provider\n114: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata has `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n115: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n116: - **THEN** the system SHALL rewrite URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Invoke via k8s provider\n119: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s`\n120: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n121: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST directly to the service endpoint from metadata\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Invoke with session header\n124: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n125: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n126: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` to the request\n127: \n128: ### Requirement: `status` command — Provider-specific status\n129: \n130: The system SHALL display status based on provider.\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Status for agentcube provider (AgentRuntime CR exists)\n133: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists\n134: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n135: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present, returning:\n136:   - `status` field value\n137:   - `agentEndpoint` if available\n138:   - Or status `created_no_status` if CR exists but no status\n139:   - Or status `not_found_in_k8s` if CR doesn't exist\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Status for k8s provider (standard deployment)\n142: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s`\n143: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` runs\n144: - **THEN** the system SHALL return Deployment and Service status including replica counts and pod status\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Status when not published\n147: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n148: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n149: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n150: \n151: ### Requirement: Error handling — Provider failures\n152: \n153: The system SHALL handle provider-specific errors appropriately.\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Kubernetes client unavailable\n156: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client fails to initialize\n157: - **WHEN** publish is attempted\n158: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the error and exit with code `1`\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness timeout\n161: - **GIVEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds 120 seconds\n162: - **WHEN** the deployment does not become ready\n163: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `TimeoutError` and record the error in metadata\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## Acceptance Criteria\n168: \n169: 1. `publish --provider agentcube` deploys via AgentRuntime CR when router_url and workload_manager_url are present\n170: 2. `publish --provider k8s` creates Deployment + NodePort Service with specified node_port, replicas, and namespace\n171: 3. `invoke` routes to correct endpoint based on provider and includes session header\n172: 4. `status` displays appropriate information for each provider type\n173: 5. Missing prerequisites (router_url, workload_manager_url) raise ValueError before deployment\n174: 6. Deployment readiness timeout works as specified (120s default)\n175: 7. Delete operations handle 404 gracefully\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: **End of Delta Spec AR-026**\n\n(End of file - total 179 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n## Overview\n\nThis spec covers the K8s/AgentCube Provider functionality in the AgentCube CLI, enabling deployment to either standard Kubernetes (Deployment + Service) or AgentCube's custom AgentRuntime CR.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-026\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: cli-toolkit/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI supports deploying agents to two target providers:\n1. **agentcube**: Uses AgentRuntime CR (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`) for deployment","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775866871657,"end":1775866871674}}}}
