{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866959034,"sessionID":"ses_286162f0cffeY8t2DF73EoXM9P","part":{"id":"prt_d79eac571001oXKf7tCL5iN4OJ","messageID":"msg_d79ea9c7d001GSH6PvEQiObJxv","sessionID":"ses_286162f0cffeY8t2DF73EoXM9P","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_936ec7bc7da64bc8a9e4660f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Tasks\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete - Implementation Pending)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Provider Selection & Prerequisites (T001-T004)\n\n- [ ] **T001** Implement `--provider` option in `publish` command (default: `agentcube`)\n  - *File:* `agentcube/cli/main.py:311-315`\n  - *Verify:* `publish --provider agentcube` uses AgentRuntime CR, `publish --provider k8s` uses Deployment+Service\n  - *Test:* Run publish with both providers and verify correct route taken\n\n- [ ] **T002** Validate `router_url` prerequisite for agentcube provider\n  - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py:293-296`\n  - *Verify:* ValueError raised when `router_url` missing in metadata\n  - *Test:* Publish with agentcube provider without router_url\n\n- [ ] **T003** Validate `workload_manager_url` prerequisite for agentcube provider  \n  - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py:293-296`\n  - *Verify:* ValueError raised when `workload_manager_url` missing in metadata\n  - *Test:* Publish with agentcube provider without workload_manager_url\n\n- [ ] **T004** Implement k8s provider options: `--node-port`, `--replicas`, `--namespace`\n  - *File:* `agentcube/cli/main.py:316-330`\n  - *Verify:* Options passed to `PublishRuntime.publish()` correctly\n  - *Test:* Verify NodePort range (30000-32767) validation\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Kubernetes Provider Deployment (T005-T009)\n\n- [ ] **T005** Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` creating Deployment + NodePort Service\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:64-172`\n  - *Verify:* Returns deployment_name, service_name, namespace, replicas, container_port, node_port, service_url\n  - *Test:* Deploy and verify K8s resources created\n\n- [ ] **T006** Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready` with 120s timeout\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:174-209`\n  - *Verify:* Polls until replicas ready or raises TimeoutError\n  - *Test:* Verify timeout raises ValueError after 120s\n\n- [ ] **T007** Implement `--node-port` specification (30000-32767)\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:89-90`\n  - *Verify:* NodePort must be in valid range\n  - *Test:* Publish with invalid node-port should fail\n\n- [ ] **T008** Implement `--replicas` specification\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:115`\n  - *Verify:* Deployment uses specified replica count\n  - *Test:* `publish --provider k8s --replicas 3` creates 3 replicas\n\n- [ ] **T009** Implement `--namespace` specification\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:26`\n  - *Verify:* Resources created in specified namespace\n  - *Test:* `publish --provider k8s --namespace myns` creates resources in `myns`\n\n- [ ] **T010** Implement `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent` with 404 handling\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:251-295`\n  - *Verify:* Returns status: \"deleted\", ignores 404 errors\n  - *Test:* Delete non-existent agent should not raise error\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: AgentCube Provider Deployment (T011-T014)\n\n- [ ] **T011** Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` with AgentRuntime CR\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:68-177`\n  - *Verify:* Creates CR with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL, sessionTimeout: \"15m\", maxSessionDuration: \"8h\", imagePullSecrets\n  - *Test:* Deploy and verify CR created with correct spec\n\n- [ ] **T012** Verify AgentRuntime CR API group/version: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:12-14`\n  - *Verify:* CR uses correct group, version, plural\n  - *Test:* Verify CRD exists in cluster\n\n- [ ] **T013** Add `imagePullSecrets` to AgentRuntime: `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:111-145`\n  - *Verify:* Spec includes imagePullSecrets\n  - *Test:* Verify in deployed CR\n\n- [ ] **T014** Implement AgentRuntime readiness probe fields from metadata\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:77-78`\n  - *Verify:* readiness_probe_path and readiness_probe_port used\n  - *Test:* Deploy with probe config verified\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: Invoke Command Routing (T015-T017)\n\n- [ ] **T015** Route invoke to AgentRuntime endpoint for agentcube provider\n  - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py:41-75`\n  - *Verify:* URL rewritten to `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n  - *Test:* Invoke with agentcube provider uses correct path\n\n- [ ] **T016** Route invoke to direct service endpoint for k8s provider\n  - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py:118-140`\n  - *Verify:* POST directly to service endpoint from metadata\n  - *Test:* Invoke with k8s provider uses direct endpoint\n\n- [ ] **T017** Add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header when session_id in metadata\n  - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py:67-73`\n  - *Verify:* Header added to HTTP request\n  - *Test:* Verify header present in request when session_id exists\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: Status Command (T018-T020)\n\n- [ ] **T018** Return agentcube status from AgentRuntime CR status field\n  - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py:60-99`\n  - *Verify:* Returns status, agentEndpoint, or \"created_no_status\" if CR exists but no status\n  - *Test:* Status shows correct CR status\n\n- [ ] **T019** Return \"not_found_in_k8s\" when AgentRuntime CR doesn't exist\n  - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py:95-99`\n  - *Verify:* Returns \"not_found_in_k8s\" for missing CR\n  - *Test:* Status for non-existent agent returns correct status\n\n- [ ] **T020** Return k8s provider status (Deployment + Service status)\n  - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py:39-58`\n  - *Verify:* Returns replica counts and pod status\n  - *Test:* Status shows deployment ready replicas\n\n---\n\n### Phase 6: Error Handling (T021-T022)\n\n- [ ] **T021** Handle Kubernetes client unavailable (exit code 1)\n  - *File:* `agentcube/cli/main.py:386-388`\n  - *Verify:* CLI prints error and exits with code 1\n  - *Test:* Verify error output and exit code\n\n- [ ] **T022** Handle deployment readiness timeout (120s) - raise TimeoutError and record in metadata\n  - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:174-209`, `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py:201-209`\n  - *Verify:* Raises TimeoutError, records error in metadata.k8s_deployment.error\n  - *Test:* Verify timeout behavior\n\n---\n\n### Phase 7: End-to-End Integration Tests (T023-T026)\n\n- [ ] **T023** Integration test: `publish --provider agentcube` with router_url and workload_manager_url\n  - *Verify:* Deploys successfully via AgentRuntime CR\n  - *Test:* Full publish flow\n\n- [ ] **T024** Integration test: `publish --provider k8s` with all options\n  - *Verify:* Creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n  - *Test:* Full publish with node-port, replicas, namespace\n\n- [ ] **T025** Integration test: `invoke` command with both providers\n  - *Verify:* Routes to correct endpoint based on provider\n  - *Test:* Invoke flow\n\n- [ ] **T026** Integration test: `status` command with both providers\n  - *Verify:* Displays appropriate information for each provider\n  - *Test:* Status flow\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Task | Depends On |\n|------|------------|\n| T002 | T001 |\n| T003 | T001 |\n| T004 | T001 |\n| T005 | T001 |\n| T006 | T005 |\n| T007 | T005 |\n| T008 | T005 |\n| T009 | T005 |\n| T010 | T005 |\n| T011 | T001 |\n| T012 | T011 |\n| T013 | T011 |\n| T014 | T011 |\n| T015 | T001 |\n| T016 | T001 |\n| T017 | T001 |\n| T018 | T011, T012 |\n| T019 |