{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866962215,"sessionID":"ses_286162f0cffeY8t2DF73EoXM9P","part":{"id":"prt_d79eb5d2f001lVWT9TcXDooh01","messageID":"msg_d79eb54e7001M2udbNuFRdNBQg","sessionID":"ses_286162f0cffeY8t2DF73EoXM9P","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_35287411b1754b46bb408039","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete - Implementation Pending)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Implementation Tasks\n11: \n12: ### Phase 1: Provider Selection & Prerequisites (T001-T004)\n13: \n14: - [ ] **T001** Implement `--provider` option in `publish` command (default: `agentcube`)\n15:   - *File:* `agentcube/cli/main.py:311-315`\n16:   - *Verify:* `publish --provider agentcube` uses AgentRuntime CR, `publish --provider k8s` uses Deployment+Service\n17:   - *Test:* Run publish with both providers and verify correct route taken\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T002** Validate `router_url` prerequisite for agentcube provider\n20:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py:293-296`\n21:   - *Verify:* ValueError raised when `router_url` missing in metadata\n22:   - *Test:* Publish with agentcube provider without router_url\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T003** Validate `workload_manager_url` prerequisite for agentcube provider  \n25:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py:293-296`\n26:   - *Verify:* ValueError raised when `workload_manager_url` missing in metadata\n27:   - *Test:* Publish with agentcube provider without workload_manager_url\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T004** Implement k8s provider options: `--node-port`, `--replicas`, `--namespace`\n30:   - *File:* `agentcube/cli/main.py:316-330`\n31:   - *Verify:* Options passed to `PublishRuntime.publish()` correctly\n32:   - *Test:* Verify NodePort range (30000-32767) validation\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ### Phase 2: Kubernetes Provider Deployment (T005-T009)\n37: \n38: - [ ] **T005** Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` creating Deployment + NodePort Service\n39:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:64-172`\n40:   - *Verify:* Returns deployment_name, service_name, namespace, replicas, container_port, node_port, service_url\n41:   - *Test:* Deploy and verify K8s resources created\n42: \n43: - [ ] **T006** Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready` with 120s timeout\n44:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:174-209`\n45:   - *Verify:* Polls until replicas ready or raises TimeoutError\n46:   - *Test:* Verify timeout raises ValueError after 120s\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T007** Implement `--node-port` specification (30000-32767)\n49:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:89-90`\n50:   - *Verify:* NodePort must be in valid range\n51:   - *Test:* Publish with invalid node-port should fail\n52: \n53: - [ ] **T008** Implement `--replicas` specification\n54:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:115`\n55:   - *Verify:* Deployment uses specified replica count\n56:   - *Test:* `publish --provider k8s --replicas 3` creates 3 replicas\n57: \n58: - [ ] **T009** Implement `--namespace` specification\n59:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:26`\n60:   - *Verify:* Resources created in specified namespace\n61:   - *Test:* `publish --provider k8s --namespace myns` creates resources in `myns`\n62: \n63: - [ ] **T010** Implement `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent` with 404 handling\n64:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:251-295`\n65:   - *Verify:* Returns status: \"deleted\", ignores 404 errors\n66:   - *Test:* Delete non-existent agent should not raise error\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ### Phase 3: AgentCube Provider Deployment (T011-T014)\n71: \n72: - [ ] **T011** Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` with AgentRuntime CR\n73:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:68-177`\n74:   - *Verify:* Creates CR with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL, sessionTimeout: \"15m\", maxSessionDuration: \"8h\", imagePullSecrets\n75:   - *Test:* Deploy and verify CR created with correct spec\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T012** Verify AgentRuntime CR API group/version: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n78:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:12-14`\n79:   - *Verify:* CR uses correct group, version, plural\n80:   - *Test:* Verify CRD exists in cluster\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T013** Add `imagePullSecrets` to AgentRuntime: `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n83:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:111-145`\n84:   - *Verify:* Spec includes imagePullSecrets\n85:   - *Test:* Verify in deployed CR\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T014** Implement AgentRuntime readiness probe fields from metadata\n88:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:77-78`\n89:   - *Verify:* readiness_probe_path and readiness_probe_port used\n90:   - *Test:* Deploy with probe config verified\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ### Phase 4: Invoke Command Routing (T015-T017)\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T015** Route invoke to AgentRuntime endpoint for agentcube provider\n97:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py:41-75`\n98:   - *Verify:* URL rewritten to `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n99:   - *Test:* Invoke with agentcube provider uses correct path\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T016** Route invoke to direct service endpoint for k8s provider\n102:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py:118-140`\n103:   - *Verify:* POST directly to service endpoint from metadata\n104:   - *Test:* Invoke with k8s provider uses direct endpoint\n105: \n106: - [ ] **T017** Add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header when session_id in metadata\n107:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py:67-73`\n108:   - *Verify:* Header added to HTTP request\n109:   - *Test:* Verify header present in request when session_id exists\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ### Phase 5: Status Command (T018-T020)\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T018** Return agentcube status from AgentRuntime CR status field\n116:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py:60-99`\n117:   - *Verify:* Returns status, agentEndpoint, or \"created_no_status\" if CR exists but no status\n118:   - *Test:* Status shows correct CR status\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T019** Return \"not_found_in_k8s\" when AgentRuntime CR doesn't exist\n121:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py:95-99`\n122:   - *Verify:* Returns \"not_found_in_k8s\" for missing CR\n123:   - *Test:* Status for non-existent agent returns correct status\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T020** Return k8s provider status (Deployment + Service status)\n126:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py:39-58`\n127:   - *Verify:* Returns replica counts and pod status\n128:   - *Test:* Status shows deployment ready replicas\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ### Phase 6: Error Handling (T021-T022)\n133: \n134: - [ ] **T021** Handle Kubernetes client unavailable (exit code 1)\n135:   - *File:* `agentcube/cli/main.py:386-388`\n136:   - *Verify:* CLI prints error and exits with code 1\n137:   - *Test:* Verify error output and exit code\n138: \n139: - [ ] **T022** Handle deployment readiness timeout (120s) - raise TimeoutError and record in metadata\n140:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:174-209`, `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py:201-209`\n141:   - *Verify:* Raises TimeoutError, records error in metadata.k8s_deployment.error\n142:   - *Test:* Verify timeout behavior\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ### Phase 7: End-to-End Integration Tests (T023-T026)\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T023** Integration test: `publish --provider agentcube` with router_url and workload_manager_url\n149:   - *Verify:* Deploys successfully via AgentRuntime CR\n150:   - *Test:* Full publish flow\n151: \n152: - [ ] **T024** Integration test: `publish --provider k8s` with all options\n153:   - *Verify:* Creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n154:   - *Test:* Full publish with node-port, replicas, namespace\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T025** Integration test: `invoke` command with both providers\n157:   - *Verify:* Routes to correct endpoint based on provider\n158:   - *Test:* Invoke flow\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T026** Integration test: `status` command with both providers\n161:   - *Verify:* Displays appropriate information for each provider\n162:   - *Test:* Status flow\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## Dependencies\n167: \n168: | Task | Depends On |\n169: |------|------------|\n170: | T002 | T001 |\n171: | T003 | T001 |\n172: | T004 | T001 |\n173: | T005 | T001 |\n174: | T006 | T005 |\n175: | T007 | T005 |\n176: | T008 | T005 |\n177: | T009 | T005 |\n178: | T010 | T005 |\n179: | T011 | T001 |\n180: | T012 | T011 |\n181: | T013 | T011 |\n182: | T014 | T011 |\n183: | T015 | T001 |\n184: | T016 | T001 |\n185: | T017 | T001 |\n186: | T018 | T011, T012 |\n187: | T019 | T018 |\n188: | T020 | T005 |\n189: | T021 | T001 |\n190: | T022 | T006 |\n191: | T023 | T001, T002, T003, T011 |\n192: | T024 | T001, T005, T007, T008, T009 |\n193: | T025 | T015, T016, T017 |\n194: | T026 | T018, T020 |\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## Verification Checklist\n199: \n200: - [ ] `publish --provider agentcube` deploys via AgentRuntime CR when router_url and workload_manager_url are present\n201: - [ ] `publish --provider k8s` creates Deployment + NodePort Service with specified node_port, replicas, and namespace\n202: - [ ] `invoke` routes to correct endpoint based on provider and includes session header\n203: - [ ] `status` displays appropriate information for each provider type\n204: - [ ] Missing prerequisites (router_url, workload_manager_url) raise ValueError before deployment\n205: - [ ] Deployment readiness timeout works as specified (120s default)\n206: - [ ] Delete operations handle 404 gracefully\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## References\n211: \n212: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md`\n213: - Base Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n(End of file - total 213 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Tasks\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete - Implementation Pending)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Provider Selection & Prerequisites (T001-T004)\n\n- [ ] **T001** Implement `--provider` option in `publish` command (default: `agentcube`)\n  - *File:* `agentcube/cli/main.py:311-315`\n  - *Verify:* `publish --provider agentcube` uses AgentRuntime CR, `publish --provider k8s` uses Deployment+Service\n  - *Test:* Run publish with both providers and verify correct route taken\n\n- [ ] **T002** Validate `router_url` prerequisite for agentcube provider\n  - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py:293-296`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775866962196,"end":1775866962211}}}}
